headline.main: The City of New-York-Its Growth and Destiny.

docs.lead_paragraph: New-York is leaping forward in the race for wealth and greatness, more rapidly than at any other period of her history. She intimately sympathizes with the general prosperity ofthe country, and advances with it.

docs.lead_paragraph: ROBBERY ON SHIP-B0ARD.--On Saturday, Officer CURLEY, of the Sixth Ward, arrested for men named PATRICK DOUGHERTY, THOMAS MURPHY, DAVID ROSTER, and JOHN RYAN, charged with stealing a carpet bag from on board the packet-ship Rialto, from Liverpool, containing four ten pound Bank of England notes, valued at $200; also some shirts, and a portable writing-desk, valued at $7-in all $207, the property of THOMAS CULEY.

headline.main: Festival of the St. George's Society.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Sixty-Seventh Anniversary of St. George's Society, of New-York, was celebrated on Saturday evening, by a sumptuous banquet at the Astor-House. At the head of the large dining hall was a full length portrait of Queen VICTORIA, copied from VANDERHOFFER'S celebrated painting.

headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times. FROM WASHINGTON. Tehuantepec Treaty Received--Santa Anna's Disposition--The Question of Validity--Political Operations--Foreign Missions--Dix and Dillaye likely to Succeed.

docs.lead_paragraph: Major ITERBIDE, the son of the Emperor, has arrived in this City from the City of Mexico, as bearer of dispatches to the Mexican Minister, and bringing from our Minister, Judge CONKLING, to the State Department, a copy of the Treaty negotiated by him with Commissioners TORNELL and LONSAS, guaranteeing and protecting the SLOOgrant for the Tehuantepec Railroad.
